main event: A civilian (police) in Englewood, Ohio observed a light moving north then east, similar in magnitude to a satellite, and a jet-like object at high altitude around 40,000 feet.
interesting points: The observer was out on his patio interested in the moon and had binoculars.
The light moving north then east was similar in magnitude to a satellite.
The observer was convinced the high-altitude object was a jet.
The observation took place in Englewood, Ohio, which is described as out in the country.
sighted object: a light moving north then east, similar to a satellite, and a jet-like object at high altitude
